- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with anomaly detection in social and web networks.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for anomaly detection.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses the Hopfield network model of memory to combine graph and time information.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with the detection and tracking of anomalous activity in a dynamic network.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category as anomaly detection is often used in security applications.
